{"lemma":"بُعْدَيْ","slug":"بُعْدَيْ","root":"ب.ع.د","root_slug":"ب-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ع-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بُعْد","root":"بعد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adv","noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2867"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be distant, afar, to become distant, go away (مِنْ (min) or عَنْ (ʕan) from)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to die, to perish"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَعُدَ (baʕuda) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dimension"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"absence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"death"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"interval"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَعَدَ (baʕada) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَعِدَ (baʕida) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distance, going to a distance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"death"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"after"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"after that","examples":[{"text":"فَمَا يُكَذِّبُكَ بَعْدُ بِالدِّينِ","english":"So what will make you deny the religion after that?"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2867","headword_ar":"بَعْدِى","root":"bEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like are also frequently used as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda EahodiY","text_ar":"بَعْدَ عَهْدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like; as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado tagay~arota baEodY","text_ar":"قَدْ تَغَيَّرْتَ بَعْدى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast become altered since I knew thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saw thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"met thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was with thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"And similar to this are many phrases in the Kur; as, for instance, in ii. 48,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a A@t~axa*otumu A@lEijola mino baEodihi","text_ar":"ثُمَّ ا@تَّخَذْتُمُ ا@لعِجْلَ مِنْ بَعْدِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then ye took to yourselves the calf"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a god, or an object of worship,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely Moses, i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after his having gone away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aA baEodu","text_ar":"اَمَّا بَعْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, &c.) is [an expression denoting transition;] an expression by which an address or a discourse is divided; (S;) used without any complement to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bEd","text_ar":"بعد"},{"kind":"text","text":", which in this case signifies the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabolu","text_ar":"قَبْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aA baEodu faqado kaAna ka*aA","text_ar":"اَمَّا بَعْدُ فَقَدْ كَانَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Now, after these preliminary words,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l- 'Abbás in TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiTaAbN","text_ar":"خِطَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) I proceed to say, that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a thing has happened:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after my prayer for thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after praising God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the first who used this formula was David; (K;) or Jacob; (TA;) or Kaab Ibn-Lu-eí; (K;) or Kuss Ibn-Sá'ideh; or Yaarub Ibn-Kahtán. (TA.) ―         -b2-  You also use the dim. form, saying ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEayodahu","text_ar":"بُعَيْدَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A little after him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"], when you mean by it to denote a time near to the preceding time. (Msb.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonK","text_ar":"بَيْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu buEayodaAti","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ بُعَيْدَاتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiydaAtihi","text_ar":"بَعِيدَاتِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEayodaAtih","text_ar":"بُعَيْدَاتِه"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him a little after a separation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after intervals of separation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after a while."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahaA lataDoHaku","text_ar":"اـِنَّهَا لَتَضْحَكُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonK","text_ar":"بَيْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEayo*aAti","text_ar":"بُعَيْذَاتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily she laughs after intervals."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byn","text_ar":"بين"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEayodaAt","text_ar":"بُعَيْدَات","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used only as an adv. n. of time. (S, L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEodu","text_ar":"بَعْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also sometimes means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Now; yet; as yet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [It is used in this sense mostly in negative phrases; as, for instance, in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yamuto baEodu","text_ar":"لَمْ يَمُتْ بَعْدُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not died yet."},{"kind":"text","text":"The following is one of the instances of its having this meaning in affirmative phrases:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~iya AlHawoliY~u","text_ar":"سُمِّيَ الحَوْلِىُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^awolaAdi Albaqari tabiyEFA liA^an~ahu yanobaEu A^um~ahu baEodu","text_ar":"مِنْ اَوْلَادِ البَقَرِ تَبِيعًا لِاَنَّهُ يَنْبَعُ اُمَّهُ بَعْدُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The yearling of the offspring of cows is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbyE","text_ar":"تبيع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because he yet follows his mother:"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurring in the Mgh &c., in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbE","text_ar":"تبع"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  It occurs also in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa","text_ar":"مَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the words of the Kur [ii. 174 and v. 95],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famani A@EotadaY baEoda *`lika","text_ar":"فَمَنِ ا@عْتَدَى بَعْدَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., (as some say, MF,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa *lk","text_ar":"مَعَ ذلك"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And whoso transgresseth notwithstanding that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b5-  It has been said that it also means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Before, in time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus bearing two contr. significations: that it has this meaning in two instances; in the Kur [lxxix. 30], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A@loA^aroDa baEoda *`lika","text_ar":"وَ ا@لْاَرْضَ بَعْدَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daHaAhaA","text_ar":"دَحَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the earth, before that, He spread it forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and [xxi. 105] where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaqado katabonaA fiY A@lz~abuwri mino baEodi A@l*~ikori","text_ar":"وَلَقَدْ كَتَبْنَا فِى ا@لزَّبُورِ مِنْ بَعْدِ ا@لذِّكْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily we wrote in the Psalms before the Kur-án"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (MF, TA:) but Az says that this is a mistake; that God created the earth not spread forth; then created the heaven; and then spread forth the earth: (L, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*kr","text_ar":"الذكر"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the latter of these instances means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Book of the Law revealed to Moses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alzbwr","text_ar":"الزبور"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the revealed Scriptures;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*kr","text_ar":"الذكر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Preserved Tablet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd,) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Original of the Scriptures,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is with God. (Jel.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","S","L","MF","Bd"]}]}}